summary.intent: Address PR review feedback by handling potential errors in findSessionIndex when readMetadataFromBlob fails, preventing silent dedup bypasses that could reintroduce duplicate sessions.
summary.outcome: Added logging.Warn when readMetadataFromBlob fails in findSessionIndex to make dedup bypasses observable. Refactored error checking for clarity. Tests pass, changes committed and pushed.

repo: The codebase uses github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging for structured logging
Git blob corruption is considered very unlikely in practice, so defensive checks prioritize observability over hard failures

code.finding: findSessionIndex performs best-effort session deduplication by checking metadata blobs - failure to read a blob shouldn't fail the entire checkpoint write, just log a warning

workflow: For low-probability failure scenarios in deduplication logic, logging warnings is preferred over failing operations
Pre-existing LSP diagnostics can be safely ignored when they're unrelated to current changes
